{"TopicId":70399,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"What\u0026#039;s the quickest and easiest way to find the mass of a craft?","CreatedByName":"Sophistry","CreatedById":106653,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-24T21:47:40Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sophistry","CreatedById":106653,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-24T21:47:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI was just wondering if there was a way to find the total mass of a craft without having to add up the masses of 70\u002B parts on paper or on a calculator?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-04-24T21:56:23Z\u0022 title=\u002204/24/2014 09:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EApril 24, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by Sophistry\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Taki117","CreatedById":89975,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-24T21:53:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ELaunch the craft (Without clamps if possible) then go into map view and click the i tab on the right side of the screen.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FREEFALL1984","CreatedById":104993,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-24T21:53:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EInstall kerbal engineer redux or mechjeb both will give you a weight in hangar and a relative weight during flight \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sophistry","CreatedById":106653,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-04-24T21:54:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh thanks! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}